Devfest Nantes 2016 > The GDG Nantes Team

The GDG Nantes TEAM

The Google Developers Groups (GDGs) are groups of people interested in Google Platforms and Technologies: Android, Chrome, Google Apps, Angular, Cloud, AppEngine... These groups promoting sharing can be found all around the world.

The objective of GDG Nantes is to organise events regularly:

  • Google Technology Conferences and others on the Web, Cloud, Mobile.
  • Informal theme-based evening sessions around an Aperitif to facilitate meetings of similar minds and thoughts
  • Competitions (Hackathon, ...)

The Volunteers of DevFest

Each year, Epitech Nantes student volunteers help the GDG team to set up the venue, the organization, the welcome, logistics and preparation of the event. We would like to thank them for their enthusiastic help!

Nantes Tech

The city of Nantes is increasingly becoming a popular centre for new technology with regularly organised events, conferences proposed in a friendly environment.

These events put in place new Web technologies, cloud solutions and Connected Objects products. They also aim at improving the tech development in the Western regions of France, to participate in local professional dynamism, and to make Nantes a nationally recognized competence center in the field of new technologies.

Nantes is recognised and certified as among the premier cities in the French Tech; it is one of the most dynamic ecosystems of France in terms of web and digital innovation.
